<I c="LootActions" i="action" m="interactions.utils.loot" n="loot_EP20World_AskAbout" s="463168">
  <L n="loot_actions">
    <V t="notification_and_dialog">
      <U n="notification_and_dialog">
        <V n="dialog" t="notification">
          <U n="notification">
            <L n="dialog_options">
              <E>DISABLE_CLOSE_BUTTON</E>
            </L>
            <V n="icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="resource_key">
                <U n="resource_key">
                  <T n="key" p="InEP20\UI\Icons\Headlines\headline_CryptidTrack.png">2f7d0004:00000000:a0c4011cda6296e8</T>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="secondary_icon" t="enabled">
              <V n="enabled" t="participant">
                <U n="participant">
                  <L n="participant_type">
                    <E>Actor</E>
                  </L>
                </U>
              </V>
            </V>
            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xA96CA274<!--String: "You should check out Underlight Bay in the Jellyfish Junction neighborhood! There's the Glow and Flow Festival there every new moon at 7pm!"--></T>
                  <T>0x512266C3<!--String: "Over in Crystal Valley, there are the remains of Scoop's Gold Mine and out in front of it, you'll sometimes see Buddy Scoop the Collector Kid. Buddy should be there from about 10am - 6pm, just as long as he's not taking his sweet time getting to his table. That kiddo gets sidetracked looking for frogs sometimes!"--></T>
                  <T>0xBE27A790<!--String: "Over in Wanderwood Wilds, there's a geyser called Hothead Rock Geyser. The geyser will blow a few times a day—you should check the Ranger Station for current conditions—and if you go through a special Adventure Quest from Toshie, the Storyteller, you'll learn about a special thing you can do to make the geyser get red-hot!"--></T>
                  <T>0x6489E218<!--String: "You'll find Camp Gibbi Gibbi over in Wanderwood Wilds, and it's definitely the perfect neighborhood for a camp. So many trees and so much vegetation! If you get lost, keep an eye out for the Old Firewatch Tower. You'll also find a Sim nearby there: the Lost Adventurer."--></T>
                  <T>0xBFD5313B<!--String: "Over in Jellyfish Junction you'll find Toshie Akamine, the Storyteller Sim, who is usually over by the Story Map. She can clue you into some Adventure Quests and tell you a little more about landmarks in Gibbi Point."--></T>
                  <T>0x3DCBD1D<!--String: "Gibbi Point is known for Plumbirds, but they tend to hide and be a little less visible these days. Though there's a giant Plumbird hanging out near a nest in Crystal Valley—you should look for her nest for some quests to learn more about Plumbirds."--></T>
                  <T>0xE3DAE7C4<!--String: "Jellyfish Junction is known as an artisan haven, with some unusual sculptures plus opportunities for papercrafting when you visit. You can also shop at Makin' Paper for purchasable papercraft objects, or stop by This Oar That Shop for kayaking supplies."--></T>
                  <T>0x8A98B1EA<!--String: "Fitness Fest is every Monday - Wednesday in Jellyfish Junction.\nThe Glow and Flow Festival is every New Moon in Jellyfish Junction.\nThe Sunrise, Sunset Festival takes place on weekends in Crystal Valley.\nThe 'Round the Fire Festival takes place on weekends in Wanderwood Wilds."--></T>
                </L>
              </U>
            </V>
            <V n="title" t="disabled" />
            <E n="visual_type">SPEECH</E>
          </U>
        </V>
      </U>
    </V>
  </L>
